        etag - http header, identifier for a specific version of a resource
        lastModified - http header, used to determine if a resource hasn't been modified since
        cacheControl - http header, used to determine cache strategy of a resource
        expires - http header, used to determine when a resource is stale
        retryAfter - http header, used to indicate when the service is expected to be unavailable to the client
